PID Manager

See INSTALL file for installation instructions.
See interface.txt file for interface descriptions.

Call ant target 'doc' (~> ant doc) to create the pdf concept documentation 
of the PIDManager.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
!!! Attention: Do not distribute private admin key (admpriv.bin) !!!
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

If generator method is set to 'debug' then is only the suffix test-handle-123:2 
created. This is useful to prevent depredation of namespaces through tests.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The etc/ directory contains some examples for properties files.


Building from the Source
----------------------------
Requirements:
	- Installed Java Environment (>= Java 1.5)
	- Installed Apache Ant (>= version 1.7)
Grab the source either from the Repository or as compressed file from the web page.
Jump to the project root directory and call ant to get an overview of all targets.

~> ant

 - help
 	Prints a brief help for each target. 
 - doc
 	Compiles the documentation to pdf.
 - jar 
 	Creates an Java Archive (jar) without depending libraries.
 - onejar
 	Compiles the PIDManager to one jar file which includes all depending libraries.
 - ear
 	Creates an Enterprise Archive (ear) with depending libraries and default 
 	configuration files.
 - war
 	Creates an Web Archive with depending libraries and default configuration files.
 - compile
 	Compiles the Java classes.
 	 
